        public static java.nio.file.Path getDefaultDir()

        default path.

      • setDefaultDir

        public static boolean setDefaultDir(java.nio.file.Path p)
        setter method of default path. this method is thread safe.
        Note:- changes made in default path is not reflected in existing objects of the class as they use their local variable to store path variable to locate the data files.
        Parameters:
        p - new default path.
        Returns:
        true if the default path is updated with p, false if p is not absolute or not a directory.

      • comp

        private void comp(TestState us)
        this method compare the output of us with corresponding output in list orig. this method finds the equivalent original output from list orig and compare it's output to the output of us.
        Parameters:
        us - object of TestState, output of which is going to be compared.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no equivalent object exist in list orig or us contain invalid information like negative programID or index etc..
